    "id": "xc-3564",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2021-09-22",
    "title": "Boys Finish 3rd Out of 46 Schools at Boardman - Girls 33rd",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Girls Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The boys cross country team ran a great race on Saturday finishing 3rd out of 46 schools from 3 states at the Boardman Spartan Invitational.  Boardman is one of the biggest meets around and the course was tough with high humidity. The team only trailed North Allegheny of Pennsylvania and Cleveland St. Ignatius in the team standings.  The team was led in scoring by Kyle Woods, Connor Reed,  Alex Hill, Cooper Reed, and Dominic Carosielli.  \n\nThe girls finished 33rd overall and were lead in scoring by Jenna Halco, Kylie Miller, Bella Troyer, Macey Foss, and Brooke Lieser.\n\nThe JV teams will compete this weekend at Strongsville with the varsity taking a week off of racing.  They'll be back in action at GlenOak on Saturday October 2nd for the Stark County Championships.  \n\n[Full Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/ccevent.php?peventid=81&table=C)",
