    "id": "xc-3495",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2020-11-02",
    "title": "Regional Meet Results: Kyle Woods Qualifies to State Finishing 25th, Emily Beck Finishes 56th",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Girls Meet Results",
      "Honors"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "This past weekend Kyle Woods and Emily Beck raced at Boardman in the Cross Country Northeast Regional Championship.  It was the toughest conditions they've raced in this year and at the end of the day Kyle finished 25th overall and qualified to the State Meet by finishing in the top 32 and Emily finished an impressive 56th overall.  Kyle is the 12th boy in school history to qualify to the state meet.  He'll compete at Fortress Obetz on Saturday. This is the first year the meet will be held there.  Good luck Kyle and Go Perry!\n\n[Boys Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/reg/young/2020/b1.pdf)\n\n[Girls Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/reg/young/2020/g1.pdf)",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
