    "id": "xc-3418",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2020-09-28",
    "title": "Boys Varsity and JV Teams Both Finish 3rd at Strongsville",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "The Boys Cross Country team competed at the Strongsville Vertical Runner Invitational on Saturday.  The varsity team finished 3rd place overall behind Medina Highland and Solon finishing just in front of Brunswick and Medina. The team was lead in scoring by Kyle Woods (5th), Connor Reed (7th), Alex Hill (16th), Cooper Reed (39th), and Dominic Carosielli (50th).  Kyle (16:26), Connor (16:29), and Alex (16:57) all ran personal bests as well as Austin Hammock (17:52) and Thomas Haren (18:37) in the varsity race. \n\nThe JV Boys team also finished 3rd place at Strongsville lead by a 10th place finish from Spencer Wright. He was followed in scoring by Nathan Singo (22nd), Abe Fleischaker (25th), Joe Backus (33rd), and Grayson Hilderbrandt (42nd).  Nathan (19:05) and Joe (19:19) both ran personal best as well.  Riley Hostetler (20:02), Hayden Giaque (20:22), and Cameron Cooper (22:18) also ran personal bests.\n\nThe team will race at GlenOak on Saturday at the Start County Championships.\n\n[Results](https://results.raceroster.com/results/b6gpgq46rnx5rzkc)",
