    "id": "xc-3402",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2020-09-14",
    "title": "Boy Finish 5th, Girls 6th at GlenOak Early Season Federal Invite",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Girls Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The boys cross country team finished 5th on Saturday at GlenOak in the Early Season Federal League Invite.  The team was lead by Connor Reed - 6th, Kyle Woods - 10th, Alex Hill - 13th, Cooper Reed - 16th, and Austin Hammock - 37th in scoring.  The team finished just a few points behind multiple teams in a very competitive small meet.  Personal best times were turned in on a hot, tough day by Connor Reed, Austin Hammock, Nathan Singo, and Cameron Cooper.\n\nThe girls cross country team finished 6th at GlenOak.  They were lead in scoring by Emily Beck - 13th, Sheldyn Daugherty - 15th, Bella Troyer - 33rd, Audrey Morgan - 50th, and Jocelyn Wright - 61st.\n\nThe teams will race again this Saturday at the Boardman Spartan Invitational.\n\n[Boys Varsity Results](https://15f74757-9acd-421d-b775-c3b9024969e1.filesusr.com/ugd/3b7e39_207d1285648a4765aba12c0add85ff6d.pdf)\n\n[Girls Varsity Results](https://15f74757-9acd-421d-b775-c3b9024969e1.filesusr.com/ugd/3b7e39_879698076b7047a7bc3c31ef9cd5520b.pdf)\n\n[Boys JV Results](https://15f74757-9acd-421d-b775-c3b9024969e1.filesusr.com/ugd/3b7e39_1bc5150c085f49659bf56bc6567a9484.pdf)",
