    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2019-10-21",
    "title": "Girls Finish 5th, Boys 6th Miss Out On Qualifying to Regional Meet By One Place",
    "categories": [
      "Uncategorized"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The girls cross country team finished 5th overall out of 11 teams missing out on the 4th place qualification by 18 points.  Hannah Groff lead the way finishing 6th overall to qualify to the Regional Championship individually.  She was followed in scoring by Natalie Miller (27th), Reilly Kreger (28th), Tori Robbins (29th), and Sheldyn Daugherty (43rd).\n\nThe boys team finished 6th and missed the 5th place qualifying standard by 3 points.  Kyle Woods lead the way for the team finishing 19th overall to qualifgy to the Regional Championship individually.  He was followed in scoring by Justin Zapotoczny (27th), Devin Halter (28th), Brandon Williams (31st), and Alex Hill (40th).\n\nHannah will race at Boardman this Saturday at 12:30pm and Kyle will race at 3:00pm.\n\n[Girls Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/dist/ne/malone/2019/g1.htm)[Boys Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/dist/ne/malone/2019/b1.htm)",
    "images": [],
