    "body": "This past weekend the girls cross country team placed 5th at the Salem Early Bird Invitational. Hannah Groff lead the team with a 7th place overall finish. She was followed by Reilly Kreger with an 18th place finish. Sheldyn Daugherty 31st, Natalie Miller 33, and Tori Robbins 37th out of 155 participants.  The team will race this Saturday again at the Marlington Inviational.\n\n[Results](https://www.baumspage.com/cc/salem/2019/High%20School%20Girls%20Results.htm)",
