    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "The Boys Track team finished 3rd out of 14 schools Friday night at the Salem Cope Invitational.  The team had a pair of wins which started off with Devin Halter and Jacob Cronk finishing 1st and 2nd overall in the 3200 meter run in the first running final.  The 4x400 meter relay team of John Backus, Brandon Williams, Jamil Mills, and Izzy Morales won to close out the meet in the final event of the night.  Others who scored for the Panthers were: Jojo Lapanja, Luke Laubacher, Everett Ewing, Owen Tanzilli, Devonte Armstrong, Jaice Hill, and Kevin Echelberry.\n\nBoth the boys and girls track teams will be in action Tuesday at Jackson for their first dual meet of the season.\n\n[Results](http://www.baumspage.com/track/salem/2019/Meet%20Results.htm)",
