    "date": "2018-10-16",
    "title": "Panther Boys Finish 4th at Federal League Meet",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "The Boys Cross Country team finished 4th place overall at the Federal League Meet on Saturday running their best total team race of the season.  The team was lead by Devin Halter, Jason Lacourt, Jacob Cronk, Kyle Woods, and Everett Ewing in scoring.  Kevin Echelberry won a 6th man tiebreaker against Hoover as well. Halter and Lacourt earned 2nd Team All-Federal League while Cronk, Woods, and Ewing each earned Honorable Mention to give all 5 scorers All-Federal League status.\n\nThe Boys JV team finished 4th overall as well lead by Brandon Williams, Nick Forchione, Dominic Carosielli, Abram Fleischaker, and Owen Tanzilli.  The teams had 14 personal bests set on the day.\n\nThe varsity will compete at the District Championship this Saturday at GlenOak High School at 12:30pm",
