    "id": "xc-3155",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2018-09-24",
    "title": "Boys Finish 6th out of 26 Teams at Strongsville",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "The boys cross country team finished 6th place out of 26 schools in a very competitive field at the Strongsville Invitational on Saturday.  Devin Halter lead the way again for the team with his 20th place finish running with many of the best runners in the state. Jacob Cronk, Jason Lacourt, Everett Ewing, and Brandon Williams rounded out the scoring 5 to give the Panther's their fastest pack of the year so far despite the soggy/muddy surface. Other personal best performances on the day were turned in by Kevin Echelberry, Kyle Woods, Dom Carioselli, Spencer Wright, Nick Hill, Owen Tanzilli, Spencer Huntsman, Liam Morris, and Nathan Singo.\n\nThe team will race at GlenOak this Saturday in the Stark County Championships.  The varsity race at 10:40 and the JV at 12:00.  This is a great opportunity to see the team compete locally.",
