    "body": "The boys cross country team finished 9th overall out of 24 schools at the Strongsville Invitational on Saturday.  Joey Fedor, Jason Lacourt, Jacob Cronk, Eliott Kamerer, and Jason Williams were the scorers.  Jason Williams dropped 43 seconds off of his personal best time in the breakout performance.  Everett Ewing also had a 36 second personal best as the 6th man tie-breaker.\n\nThe girls team finished 11th overall out of 26 schools.  They were lead in scoring by Madelyn Bartolone, Grace Volpe, Andrea Hufstetler, Katie Williams, and Laura Genetin.\n\nThe teams will compete this Saturday at GlenOak High School in the Stark County Championship.\n\n[Full Results](http://www.ghgtiming.com/Website/Results/2017/Strongsville/results.html)",
