    "date": "2017-09-05",
    "title": "Both Teams Finish 2nd to GlenOak at Marlington",
    "categories": [
      "Uncategorized"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The Girls finished 2nd out of 15 schools at the Ashley White-Stumpf Invitational hosted by Marlington High School this past Saturday. Madelyn Bartolone won the race for the second year in a row. Andrea Hufstetler, Katie Williams, Grace Volpe and Elaine Bast round out the top 5 for the Lady Panthers. Madelyn was named the Canton Repository Runner of the Week.\n\nThe Boys finished 2nd place out of 19 teams led by Joey Fedor's 4th place finish. He was followed in scoring by Eliott Kamerer - 18th, Jacob Cronk - 20th, Jason Lacourt - 21st, and Jacob Peters - 28th. Kevin Echelberry, Jason Williams, and Everett Ewing each set new personal bests as well.\n\nThe teams compete again this week at Walsh Jesuit for the Pat Ritchie Inviational\n\n[Results](http://www.baumspage.com/cc/ccevent.php?peventid=26&table=C)",
