    "body": "The boys and girls track teams traveled to North Canton last night to face the Vikings. Both teams left Hoover victorious with tremendous efforts by all competitors.  Winning events for the boys were:\n\nJames Roth - 100m and 400m dash\nKeishaun Sims - High jump and 200m dash\nBen Kintz - shot put and discus\nLucas Kelley - pole vault\nJohnny Stevenson - 1600m run\nCole Morris - 3200m run\nTevion Cleveland - 300m Hurdles\nThe 4 by 100 relay team of Tevion Cleveland, James Roth, Max Baker and Keishaun Sims was also victorious.\n\nAlso scoring for the boys:  Jaret Martin, Keith Storsin, Frank Sciury, Jake Meeks, Scott Essig, Daniel Cronk, Evan Kimble, Dom Labriola and Matt Carrick.\n\nWinning events for the girls were:\nLaila Strickland - 100, 4 by 100 and 4 by 200 relay\nBekah Carr - 400, 4 by 100, 4 by 200, and 4 by 400 relay\nTaylor Anthony - 200, 4 by 100 relay\nJosie Lacourt - 4 by 100, 4 by 800 and 4 by 400 relay\nAndrea Hufstetler - 4 by 800 relay\nElaine Bast - 4 by 800 relay\nLexi Echelberry - 4 by 800 relay\nPeyton Clarke - 4 by 200 and 4 by 400 relay\nLeslie Bast - 4 by 200 and 4 by 400 relay\nMaddie Bartolone - 1600m run\nMackenzie Corrin - discus\nBekah Brown - pole vault\n\nAlso scoring for the girls:  McKenzie Spehar, Annalise Presutti, Morgan Fisher, Katie Williams, and Alexa Carpenter.\n\nGreat job by both teams on bringing home the victories!",
