    "body": "The boys and girls track teams traveled to Salem Friday night for the Salem Invitational.  The boys team finished second overall. Top 3 finishers for the panthers were:\n\nKeishaun Sims\nJames Roth\nJohnny Stevenson\nJaret Martin\nJake Meeks\nCole Morris\nTevion Cleveland\nScott Essig\nJason Lacourt\nMax Baker\nLucas Kelley\nFrank Sciury\n\nOther scorers were:\nDom Labriola, Ben Kintz, Daniel Cronk, and Evan Kimble\n\nKeishaun Sims was named the  MVP of the field events and James Roth was named MVP of the track events.\n\nThe girls team was Champions of the Salem Invitational.  Bekah Carr and Mackenzie Corrin each were champions in the 400m Dash and Discus, respectively.  Other top 3 finishers were:\n\nJosey Lacourt\nTaylor Anthony\nMorgan Fisher\nPeyton Clarke\nLeslie Bast\n\nOther scorers were:\nMackenzie Spehar, Andrea Hufstetler, Elaine Bast, Katie Williams, Grace Volpe, Selena Suarez, Annalise Presutti and Morgan Fisher\n\nBoth teams will face Hoover at North Canton Tuesday in a dual meet.  Great job to both track and field teams.",
