    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The Boys and Girls track teams faced Jackson yesterday for the first outdoor meet of the season. The Boys team fell a little short to Jackson by a score of 74 to 63.  Winning events for the boys were:\n\nLucas Kelley --  Pole Vault\nBen Kintz --  Shot Put\nMatt Carrick -- Discus\nKeishaun Sims -- High Jump\n4X100 Relay team of Tevion Cleveland, Lucas Kelley, Max Baker and Keishaun Sims\nTevion Cleveland -- 300 hurdles\nJohnny Stevenson -- 3200m Run\nChris Marx -- Wheelchair 100m , 400m and 800m\n\nThe girls team defeated Jackson by a score of 78 to 59.  It was a total team effort to knock off the polar bears.  Winning events for the girls were:\n\nJosey Lacourt -- High Jump\nMackenzie Corrin -- Shot Put and Discus\nLaila Strickland -- 100 and 200m Dash\n4X200 Relay team of Rebekah Carr, Peyton Clarke, Leslie Bast and Laila Strickland\nLexi Echelberry --  1600m Run\n4X100 Relay team of Rebekah Carr, Josey Lacourt, Taylor Anthony and Laila Strickland\nRebekah Carr --  400m Dash\n4X400 Relay team of Leslie Bast, Peyton Clarke, Josey Lacourt and Rebekah Carr.\n\nBoth teams will compete on Friday at the Salem Invitational.  Terrific job on a great start to the season.",
