    "id": "track-4178",
    "sport": "track",
    "date": "2014-06-02",
    "title": "Lucas Kelley and Tristan Williams Qualify to State Track Championship",
    "categories": [
      "Athletics"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "Lucas Kelley won the Regional Championship in pole vault with a vault of 15 feet last Wednesday at Austintown Fitch High School.  Tristan Williams finished 4th overall in the 800 meter run with a new personal best time of 1:53.70.  Both athletes qualified to the State Championship and will compete Saturday June 6th at Jesse Owens Stadium at Ohio State.  Their scoring finishes helped the Boys team finish 16th out of 42 teams who scored and ahead of 5 Federal League schools in the standings.  Charliee Strickland finished 9th in long jump.  Dominick Labriola finished 10th in shot put.  Laila Strickland finished 14th in the 200 meter dash.",
