    "date": "2014-04-21",
    "title": "Boys Finish 8th at Walsh Jesuit Warrior Relays",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Featured",
      "Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "The boys track team finished 8th at the Walsh Jesuit Warrior Relays on Saturday.  The high jump relay of Keishaun Sims, Brandon Peters, and Mitchell Paxton won.  It was the first time Mitchell had high jumped since 2011.  Tristan Williams finished 2nd in the 300 hurdles in a season best time of 39.97.  The shot put relay team of Dom Labriola, Matt Carrick, and Ryan Jackson also finished 2nd.  Others who scored were: Daniel Cronk, Nate Hamit, Nick Luzecky, Joseph Volpe, Johnny Stevenson, Alex Ryan, Tevion Cleveland, Shane Myers, and Tyler Cox.\n\n[Full Results](http://www.baumspage.com/track/walshjesuit/2014/2014%20Results.htm)\n\nCheck out Tristan's 300 meter hurdles race below:\n\nhttpvh://www.youtube.com/watch?v=werHUcXARKQ",
