    "body": "The boys cross country team were shorthanded on Saturday with Joseph Volpe missing due to the ACT test but still finished 3rd out of 11 teams at the Stow Invitational.  Tristan Williams and Mitchell Paxton lead the way finishing 5th and 6th.  Alex Ryan finished 11th overall and was followed in scoring by Johnny Stevenson in 22nd and Colton Luxenburg in 24th.  Daniel Cronk was close behind in 30th. Alex Bevington made his varsity debut finishing 39th and running a new personal best in muddy conditions.\n\nThe team will race again on Saturday at Maize Valley Farm for the Federal League Championship hosted by Lake High School.\n\n[Full Results](http://www.baumspage.com/cc/ccevent.php?peventid=268&table=C)",
