    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The Boys Cross Country Team finished 7th out of 21 teams on Saturday at the Walsh Tomahawk Run Invitational.  Tristan Williams and Joe Volpe led the way with top 25 finishes. Alex Ryan ran a new personal best and was followed closely by Mitchell Paxton.  Daniel Cronk ran another personal best to round out the top 5 scoring. Johnny Stevenson ran an outstanding race finishing just 1 second behind Daniel.  Alex Bevington finished 16th overall in the freshman race.\n\nThe girls team finished 7th out of 16 teams. Lexi Echelberry finished 17th overall to lead the team and was followed by Sydnee Fenn, Taylor Wilson, Kelsey Cobb, and Lina Partridge.  Autumn Greco finished 3rd overall in the JV race.\n\nThe teams will race again on Saturday just over the border of Pennsylvania at the Slippery Rock Invitational.\n\n[Results](http://www.baumspage.com/cc/ccevent.php?peventid=65&table=C)",
