    "body": "Both the girls and boys track teams defeated McKinley last night with the girls winning 84-53 and the boys winning 69-68.\n\nWinning events for the girls were: Taylor Wilson, Becca Backus, Kylie Church, Lina Partridge, Hannah Luke, Charliee Strickland, Lia Millin, Mikayla Dearing, Jackie Genetin, Hailey Walker, Indy Clark, Anna Oprisch, and Summer Gillard. Others scoring were: Abigail Geis, Ariel Swogger, Marissa Knop, Sydnee Fenn, and Marissa Briggs.\n\nWinning events for the boys were: Josh White, Colton Luxenburg, Brian Theis, Zach James, Mitchell Paxton, Tristan Williams, Joe Volpe, Devin Myers, and Andrew Vincent. Also scoring key points were: JoJo Tayse, Keishaun Sims, Jamie Norris, Lucas Kelley, Braxton Berry, Gage Guscoff, Alex Ryan, Ali Attar, and Shane Myers.\n\nThe boys compete tomorrow at the Walsh Jesuit Relays. Be sure to come support the teams next Saturday as Perry will host the Stark County Championships!\n\n[Canton Repository Results](http://www.cantonrep.com/highschool/x935169143/High-school-track-results-for-April-18)",
