    "id": "track-3630",
    "sport": "track",
    "date": "2012-04-21",
    "title": "Girls Win Stark County Championship! Boys Finish 3rd Overall",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Featured",
      "Girls Meet Results",
      "Honors",
      "Results"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "Perry hosted the 2012 Stark County Championships this weekend.  The Perry Girls team edged out Jackson to become Stark County Champions.  Mikayla Dearing won the 400 meter dash and also anchored the 4x200 and 4x200 relay teams with Charliee Strickland, Hailey Floom, and Jackie Genetin to 1st place finishes.  Others who scored for the girls to win the meet were: Danielle Fisher, Becca Backus, Shelby Logan, Indy Clark, Anna Oprisch, and Marissa Knop.\n\nThe boys finished 3rd out of the 21 Stark County teams and had championship performances out of Andrew Vincent in the pole vault and the 4x800 relay team of Aaron Dunn, Tyler Weisburn, Matt Mizer, and Nick Williams.  Others who scored for the boys were: Matt Thiessen, Khyler Fields, Tristan Williams, Doug Mayes, JoJo Tayse, and David Kamerer.\n\nThe teams will travel to Boardman on Tuesday for their next Federal League Dual Meet.\n\n[2012 Stark County Overall Results](http://perrylocal.org/track/files/2012/04/2012StarkCounty.htm)\n\n[2012 Stark County D2 and D3](http://perrylocal.org/track/files/2012/04/2012StarkCountyD2_D3.htm)",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
