    "date": "2012-03-27",
    "title": "Boys Win, Girls Lose against Hoover",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Featured",
      "Girls Meet Results",
      "Results"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "The track teams opened up their season tonight in a dual meet at home against Hoover. The boys won 90-47. Winning events for the boys were: Andrew Vincent, Doug Mayes, Khyler Fields, Drew Tormasi, Nick Williams, David Kamerer, Matt Mizer, Tristan Williams, Matt Thiessen, Ali Attar, Dustin DiRocco, Brenta Niera, Jamie Norris, Seth Kurzen, and Tyler Weisburn.\n\nThe girls lost to Hoover 62-75. The team had 1st place performances from: Summer Gillard, Danielle Fisher, Indy Clark, Hannah Luke, Mikayla Dearing, Hailey Floom, Jackie Genetin, and Charliee Strickland.\n\nThe boys will compete at the Ward Invitational at East Palestine High School this Saturday. The girls will be back in action with the boys as well next Tuesday at GlenOak.\n\n[Boys Results](http://perrylocal.org/track/files/2012/03/2012PerryVsHooverBoys.pdf)\n[Girls Results](http://perrylocal.org/track/files/2012/03/2012PerryVsHooverGirls.pdf)",
