    "date": "2011-03-20",
    "title": "Kyrra Eaton places 2nd and Hannah Luke places 5th at Indoor State",
    "categories": [
      "Featured",
      "Honors",
      "Results"
    ],
    "gender": "both",
    "body": "5 Perry Track Athletes competed at the Indoor State Track & Field  Championships Saturday Night at the University of Akron. The girls had 2  receive All-Ohio honors by placing in the top 8. Kyrra Eaton placed 2nd  in the state in the pole vault with a mark of 11 feet and Hannah Luke  placed 5th in the 60 meter dash with a time of 7.75.  Charlie Steiner  tied for 9th in the pole vault going 13-6 while Aaron White and Stacy  Cameron each placed 10th in the 1600 running 4:33.98 and 5:20.55  respectively.   [Full Results](http://oh.milesplit.com/meets/68369/results/150947)\n\nThe track teams will open up their outdoor season this Saturday at the GlenOak Relays.",
