    "body": "*After the Sandusky win-- heading to Cedar point.*\n\n***\n***Congratulations to the girl's cross country team!  They took first place  at the Panther Run to Fun Race in Sandusky, Ohio on Saturday.  Leading the team  and winning the race was junior Stacy Cameron with a time of 12:41.  Stacy was  followed closely by sophmore Hailey Floom, freshman Jackie Genetin and Becca  Backus, and Summer Gillard, who placed 4th, 5th, 6th and 11th respectively.   Also running well for the team were sophmore Alex Hamit, junior Tara Rodgers,  seniors Tori Machan, Maddie Shaffer and Courtney Forchione.  The girls  celebrated by spending the day at Cedar Point-- Way to go, ladies!",
