    "title": "Perry Boys place 5th and just miss state birth: Josh Tormasi qualifies as an individual",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "In Boy's Cross Country Action this past weekend at the Regional  Championship, the boy's cross country team narrowly missed the last qualifying  spot for the state meet and placed 5th.  The team was led by Josh Tormasi, who  qualified for his second state cross country meet as an individual.  Also  running outstanding races on the day and helping the team make that impressive  run were Matt Welch, Brandon Wollenberg, Justin Eddy, Cody Sundley, Shane  Gillard, and Jon Melnichenko.  Josh will run this coming Saturday at Scioto  Downs in Columbus.  Good Luck Josh!",
