    "title": "GlenOak Results and Class of 2007 Update",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "In Boy's Cross Country action this past Saturday at the GlenOak  Invitational, the Boy's Team placed 3rd out of 19 teams. Leading the team was  Brandon Wollenberg finishing 6th overall. Also, scoring for the team was Matt  Welch, Justin Eddy, Ryan Oster, and Cody Sundley. Also, winning the open race  was Shane Gillard. The team will be in action again this Saturday at the Avon  Lake Invitational.\n\nHere is a quick update of last year's seniors as well.  Ty  Griffin and J.D. Horton will be continuing their running careers at Mount Union  College and the University of Kentucky respectively.  Andrew Klecan is  attending Kent State and will pole vault there.  Other Perry Cross Country  alumni and their college choices include: Jeff Bednar (Ohio State), Evan Graham  (Toledo), Keith Stinespring (Harding, AK), and Tim Wright (Kent State Stark).",
