    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "In Boy's Track action Friday Night at Fitch, the boy's track  team finished 2nd in the Federal League Championship meet.  Leading the  way and  setting a new school record in the 4 x 800m Relay was Corwin Swint, JD  Horton,  Josh Tormasi, and Ty Griffin.  By  [running  7:51.33](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8pweVMd_SXc), they broke the old record by  over 3 seconds set 10 years ago at the State Meet.  Josh Tormasi ([in 1600m](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sJcVH2RNMZ8))  and  Andrew Klecan (in the pole vault) also picked up 1st place finishes.   Others  placing in the top 4 were Kyle Hug, Dan Harsh, Casey Sutton, Rob Dugan,  Eric  Magnacca, Dean Bradley, and Trevor Biddle. The team will be in  action again Wednesday at Hoover for the District Meet.",
