    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "In Boy's Track Action  on Saturday, the boy's track team  defended their title at the Stark County Championships.  Leading the  team to  it's 1st Place finish out of 20 teams was Andrew Klecan winning the Pole  Vault  and setting a new Stark County Meet Record.  Leading the team in points  on the  day was Eric Magnacca, who set a new school record in the 100m Dash.   Also  contributing to the outstanding team performance were Ty Griffin, Corwin  Swint,  JD Horton, Dan Harsh, Trevor Biddle, Rob Dugan, Josh Tormasi, Matt  Welch, Mario  Atkinson, and David Baughman.  The team will be in action again tomorrow  at home  against Jackson.\n\nScoring performances by the Panthers at Stark County:\n\nAndrew Klecan - pole vault - 1st 14'0\"\nEric Magnacca - 100 - 2nd 10.95, 200 2nd 22.25\nTy Griffin - 1600 - 2nd 4:25.24\nJD Horton - 3200 - 2nd 9:42.60, 1600 - 6th 4:31.05\nRob Dugan - 100 - 4th 11.34\nCorwin Swint - 800 - 4th 1:58.82\nJosh Tormasi - 800 - 5th 1:59.90, High Jump - 8th 5'10\"\nTrevor Biddle - 400 - 6th 51.79\n\nRelays:\n4x400 - 1st 3:25.83 - Trevor Biddle, Ty Griffin, Corwin Swint, Eric  Magnacca\n4x800 - 2nd 8:04.06 - Matt Welch, Ty Griffin, Josh Tormasi, Corwin Swint\n4x200 - 2nd 1:30.34 - Corwin Swint, Rob Dugan, Trevor Biddle, Eric  Magnacca\n4x100 - 5th 44.49 - Caleb Laps, Mario Atkinson, David Baughman, Rob  Dugan",
