    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "This past Saturday at  the State Indoor Track Championships, the  Perry Boys Team Placed 4th in the State.  Leading the way, earning  All-Ohio  honors and becoming Perry's first ever Individual Indoor State Champion  was J.D.  Horton winning the 3200m Run.  Also scoring and earning All-Ohio honors  were Ty  Griffin with a 4th place finish in the 1600m, Matt Welch with a 5th  place in the  3200m, and Corwin Swint with a 7th place in the 800m run.  For full  results, click[here](http://finishtiming.com/OAT-CCC/index.htm).",
