    "title": "J.D. Horton Places 34th at State Meet, All 7 Varsity Runners Receive All County Honors",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results",
      "Honors"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "J.D. Horton placed 34th this past weekend at the State Meet  running a season best 16:26.  His 34th place finish gives him the 2 highest  finishes of any Perry boy at the State Meet.\n\nAt last night's Stark County Cross Country Coaches meeting, the Perry boys came  away with\nAll-County mentions for all seven varsity runners.  Earning 1st Team  All-County were J.D. Horton, Gregory Bate, Josh Tormasi, and Ty Griffin.   Earning 2nd Team All-County were Evan Graham and Matt Welch.  Justin Eddy  rounded out the awards by earning Honorable Mention.",
