    "body": "J.D. Horton is heading back to the State Meet this Saturday at  Scioto Downs in Columbus with his 14th place overall finish this past weekend at  Regionals.  Last season, J.D. finished 20th overall becoming Perry's first  All-Ohio Cross Country Runner.  Also, sophomore Josh Tormasi's 28th place  race at Regionals earned him this week's Canton Repository Runner of the Week.\n\nGregory Bate and J.D. Horton earned 1st Team All-Federal League  status, Ty Griffin, Josh Tormasi, and Matt Welch earned 2nd Team All-Federal  League status, and Evan Graham earned Honorable Mention All-Federal League this  season.",
