  {
    "id": "xc-530",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2006-10-21",
    "title": "Horton & Tormasi Run Great Races as Team Finishes 2nd at District Meet & Qualifies for 2006 NEO Regional Meet",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "Season Best  Races were turned in by senior J.D. Horton (3rd – 16:45) and  sophomore Josh Tormasi (9th – 17:01) at the Malone District Meet  leading the Perry Boy’s Cross Country Team to a 2nd Place finish,  Qualifying the team to next Saturday’s NEO Regional Meet at Boardman.  J.D.  Horton led the way running what can be described as his breakthrough race of the  season.  Josh Tormasi recorded his first ever Top 10 finish in a Championship  Meet running as the Teams #2 runner for the first time ever. \n\n Gregory Bate (11th 17:07) and Ty Griffin (13th 17:13) both had strong Regional  Qualifying races helping Perry, for the first time ever, place 4 guys in the Top  15 at the District Meet.  Brandon Wollenberg for the 2nd week in a  row proved to be the best in the open race, bringing home the Open race title  and forcing an end of the season run-off for the team’s #7 spot.\n\nThe Team  looks forward to what many considered the most competitive Boardman Regional  Meet ever.  Many of the States Best teams will be in this year’s Regional Field.\n\nRegional Meet  Division I Race – 12:35pm at Boardman High School",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
  },
  {
    "id": "xc-532",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2006-10-16",
    "title": "Solid Pack Led by Gregory Bate Survives Hoover’s 1-4, for Close Win At Federal League Championships",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "It wasn’t  exactly the best race of the season for us on Saturday at the Federal League  Championships, but a Solid Pack was good enough to hold off Hoover for the  Federal League Title.  Hoover showed up to run on their home course and really  did some damage on us up front, out scoring us by 16 points on 1-4.  On this  cold windy day the team was led by junior Gregory Bate (7th) and J.D.  Horton (8th), followed by the pack of Ty Griffin (11th),  Josh Tormasi (14th), and Matt Welch (15th).  Both Evan  Graham and Justin Eddy had solid races for us enabling us to push Hoover’s #5  back far enough to hold on for the win. \n\n In the JV Open race, our guys really  ran their best team race of the year.  Brandon Wollenberg retained the  Individual Team Title for us winning the race in an impressive 17:57.  Cody  Sundley continued his consistent impressive racing finishing 4th.   Ryan Oster (12th), Jon Melnichenko (15th), and Keith  Stinespring (17th) all ran their best races of the season bringing  our JV team within one point of beating Hoover, placing 2nd (48-49).\nUp Next the  District Meet Sat. Oct. 21st at Malone College – Varsity Race at  12:35pm\n\nUp Next for the  JV Team will be their last race at the Walsh Jesuit Warrior JV Classic Meet\nOn Monday October 23rd at  Walsh Jesuit High School.\n9th – 10th Grade Race – 4:30pm\n11th – 12th Grade Race – 5:30pm\n\nDirections can be found [here](http://perrynet.sparcc.org/BoysXC/Documents/Walsh%20Jesuit%20Directions.pdf).",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
  },
  {
    "id": "xc-534",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2006-10-09",
    "title": "Justin Eddy, Brandon Wollenberg, & Cody Sundley Go 1-2-5 to Lead JV Team to 1st at Strongsville Invitational",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "Outstanding races were run by Justin Eddy (1st 17:16 pr), Brandon Wollenberg (2nd 17:23 pr), and Cody Sundley (5th 17:38 pr) this past Saturday at the Strongsville Invitational.  The Teams Top JV  runners were battling it out for the #7 varsity spot for this week’s upcoming  Federal League Championship meet.  The Top 3 boys ran huge PR’s in leading their  team to the JV Championship.  Corwin Swint battled an untied shoe and loose chip  the 2nd half of the race which hurt his chances to repeat as this  years individual champion, but teammate Justin Eddy ran his best finishing mile  ever to keep the JV individual championship medal with Perry again this year.   Four other set PR’s on Saturday: Kevin McDougal (18:54), Jeremy Machan (20:14),  Nick DiGiulio (20:20) and Corey Williams (20:22).\n\nThe varsity team will return to the course this Saturday  October 14th at Hoover in Quest to Beat a very impressive Boardman  and Hoover team (who just this weekend beat the state’s #3 team Chardon).",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
  },
  {
    "id": "xc-537",
    "sport": "xc",
    "date": "2006-10-02",
    "title": "Perry Boys fight the cold rain to win 2006 Stark County Championship",
    "categories": [
      "Boys Meet Results"
    ],
    "gender": "boys",
    "body": "This past Saturday, September 30, in the cold rain, the Perry  Boy’s Cross Country Team won the 2006 Stark County XC Championship, leading the  way was Junior Gregory Bate, who finished 6th overall. Greg will also be  honored this week as the Repository Boy’s Division 1 Runner of the Week.  Following Greg, with an impressive :26 1-5 split were Ty Griffin (9th), J.D.  Horton (10th), Evan Graham (16th) and Josh Tormasi (20th).\n\n The Team will sit out  their Top 6 runners this upcoming weekend at the Strongsville Invitational. The  JV Team placed 2nd to Hoover and that 2nd Place Team finish is the highest  finish the Perry Boy’s JV Team has ever placed at the County Meet. It was a “PR”  Frenzy Day for our freshmen runners, with all 5 of them setting huge PR’s. The  JV Team was led by Justin Eddy (2nd - PR), Corwin Swint (3rd) and Cody Sundley  (5th-PR). Others setting PR’s on the day were J.D. Fye, Kevin McDougal, Jeff  Bednar, Corey Williams, and Nick DiGuilio. The JV Team will be in action this  coming Saturday at the Strongsville Invitational at 12noon. The Varsity Team’s  next meet will be on Saturday October 14, at Hoover High School for the Federal  League Cross Country Championship Meet.\n\nAlso, this Friday October 6, you can see Perry Boy’s Cross Country Alumni  Runners David\nAdams (Cincinnati), Dustin Ford (Mount Union), and Mike Braucher (Akron) compete  against\none another at the All-Ohio Cross Country Championships at Ohio Wesleyan  University.",
    "images": [],
    "archived": true
  }
